WEBVTT

00:10.074 --> 00:11.739
Donna...

00:12.870 --> 00:14.223
Donna.

00:14.224 --> 00:15.557
You know, in all the years
that we worked together,

00:15.559 --> 00:17.225
you've been over
to my place exactly twice,

00:17.227 --> 00:18.660
the God-awful
dinner party and...

00:18.662 --> 00:19.761
the other time.

00:19.763 --> 00:21.029
I have been gone
three weeks,

00:21.031 --> 00:23.131
and you've been here
that many times. What?

00:23.133 --> 00:24.733
I had a good time
at that dinner party.

00:24.735 --> 00:26.935
Oh, my God, it is
just like you to make a joke.

00:26.937 --> 00:28.937
And ignore the other time.

00:31.007 --> 00:33.141
I brought you
your bonus.

00:36.779 --> 00:38.446
Really?
You thought that

00:38.448 --> 00:39.848
would make it all better,
handing me a check?

00:39.850 --> 00:41.449
Look, I know that
you're pissed.

00:41.451 --> 00:43.218
- Oh, what gave it away?
- Donna...

00:43.220 --> 00:45.787
You just had to jump in there
at the trial, didn't you?

00:45.789 --> 00:47.923
You just had to fight
my battles for me.

00:47.925 --> 00:49.824
Yeah, I did that because,
the last time I saw you,

00:49.826 --> 00:51.660
you were pissed that
I didn't fight for you.

00:51.662 --> 00:53.461
Well, congratulations, Harvey.
All you managed to do

00:53.463 --> 00:56.031
was make it look
like I love you.

00:56.033 --> 00:57.599
Oh, Jesus Christ.

00:57.601 --> 01:00.001
Oh, my God,
you think I do.

01:02.139 --> 01:05.507
I have actually never met
such a self-important--

01:05.509 --> 01:07.776
Donna, about that time,
you once told me--

01:07.778 --> 01:09.644
I don't care what
I once told you!

01:09.646 --> 01:10.979
That wasn't
what Louis was asking.

01:10.981 --> 01:12.314
He was asking if
I love you.

01:12.316 --> 01:13.782
And you wouldn't answer.

01:13.784 --> 01:15.383
Because he was forcing
a yes or no answer

01:15.385 --> 01:18.453
to a complicated question.

01:18.455 --> 01:21.923
I am not in love
with you, Harvey.

01:23.059 --> 01:25.427
I love you
like a brother

01:25.429 --> 01:26.962
or a cousin,
somebody that

01:26.964 --> 01:29.297
you really, really look forward
to seeing at Christmas,

01:29.299 --> 01:31.499
and then you're really,
really glad to see leave.

01:31.501 --> 01:33.435
And as far as
you and I are concerned,

01:33.437 --> 01:34.836
Christmas is over.

01:34.838 --> 01:36.471
I didn't just come here
to give you a check.

01:36.473 --> 01:37.939
I came here
to get you back.

01:37.941 --> 01:39.307
What, Cameron
not working out?

01:39.309 --> 01:41.243
I heard that little shit
redid my entire filing system.

01:41.245 --> 01:43.845
Cameron's fine.
Look, I need you.

01:43.847 --> 01:47.215
- Need?
- Need.

01:47.217 --> 01:48.817
- Well, what about Jessica?
- Already signed off.

01:48.819 --> 01:50.185
How did you get her
to do that?

01:50.187 --> 01:54.422
Because I told her
I can't be me without you.

01:55.925 --> 01:58.793
- No, you didn't.
- Well, I thought it.

01:58.795 --> 02:00.562
And she knows it.

02:00.564 --> 02:01.963
Okay, I will come back
on two conditions.

02:01.965 --> 02:05.800
One is you replace that check
with a bigger one.

02:05.802 --> 02:08.902
And the other?

02:15.378 --> 02:16.845
Harold...

02:16.847 --> 02:20.348
Is that porn?
No.

02:20.350 --> 02:22.717
Well, yes, but that's not
what I'm using it for.

02:22.719 --> 02:24.286
Okay, I'm about 150% sure

02:24.288 --> 02:27.155
that I'm gonna
regret this, but...

02:27.157 --> 02:28.189
What are you using it for?

02:28.191 --> 02:30.025
I'm looking at tattoos.

02:30.027 --> 02:31.926
I told you, it's what
I'm getting with my first--

02:31.928 --> 02:34.863
Bonus time,
boys and girls.

02:34.865 --> 02:37.866
Too much.
<i>Way</i> too much.

02:37.868 --> 02:42.103
Oof, multiply this by zero,
and it's still way too much.

02:42.105 --> 02:44.272
O'Neil, Racine,

02:44.274 --> 02:47.342
Sabbatini...
no Ross.

02:47.344 --> 02:49.044
- Very funny, Louis.
- I'm not kidding.

02:49.046 --> 02:51.546
It looks like
you came up empty.

02:58.187 --> 03:00.188
You have the file for
the Solis motion to dismiss?

03:00.190 --> 03:02.857
Yep, all set.
Main citations are tabbed.

03:02.859 --> 03:06.361
Good. Go.
I'm busy.

03:06.363 --> 03:08.763
Okay, I was just, um...

03:08.765 --> 03:11.299
you know, before,
um...you--

03:11.301 --> 03:13.668
Are you having a stroke?

03:13.670 --> 03:15.203
What?
My bonus.

03:15.205 --> 03:16.771
Louis didn't have it.

03:16.773 --> 03:18.640
Well, at least, he said
that he didn't have it,

03:18.642 --> 03:20.241
so I thought
that maybe you, uh...

03:20.243 --> 03:22.377
Maybe Jessica thinks
you don't deserve one.

03:22.379 --> 03:25.046
You know, because...
you're not a lawyer.

03:25.048 --> 03:28.416
Right, right.
No, that's true, so I guess

03:28.418 --> 03:29.918
these won't be
doing you any good.

03:29.920 --> 03:31.186
Jessica thinks
you're not a lawyer.

03:31.188 --> 03:33.188
I don't think that.

03:37.593 --> 03:41.162
Um...wow.

03:41.164 --> 03:43.631
Your Monica Eton
performance worked.

03:43.633 --> 03:47.001
You switched Carson,
Gallo, and Fogerty.

03:47.003 --> 03:48.336
Wait, is that why
you're giving me so much?

03:48.338 --> 03:50.171
Yes. We're up one.

03:50.173 --> 03:51.606
You might want to
hold onto it for a bit.

03:51.608 --> 03:53.007
- Why?
- Hanson.

03:53.009 --> 03:54.109
Took a job at
the Justice Department.

03:54.111 --> 03:57.178
Our lead is gone.
Now we're even.

03:59.049 --> 04:01.182
Well, the vote's
in four days.

04:01.184 --> 04:04.152
The tie goes to the incumbent.
So we're good.

04:04.154 --> 04:08.089
- Probably.
- Nice.

04:08.091 --> 04:10.358
Uh, you do realize that
"hold onto it for a bit" thing,

04:10.360 --> 04:12.527
that's just
a figure of speech.

04:12.529 --> 04:16.664
Yeah, okay,
I'm just...

04:24.508 --> 04:25.974
You wanted to see me?

04:25.976 --> 04:29.210
Saw you handing out bonuses
to the associates earlier.

04:29.212 --> 04:31.813
They must all
be feeling grateful.

04:31.815 --> 04:33.648
The firm was
quite generous.

04:33.650 --> 04:36.451
It's not just the associates
who should be rewarded.

04:36.453 --> 04:37.719
Well, for me personally,
it's the satisfaction

04:37.721 --> 04:39.487
of the work
that drives me.

04:39.489 --> 04:42.457
Although the money
does help keep score.

04:42.459 --> 04:43.525
You misunderstand me.

04:43.527 --> 04:44.893
I don't have a check
for you, Louis.

04:44.895 --> 04:48.730
I was hoping
you had one for me.

04:48.732 --> 04:49.864
I'm sorry,
I'm confused.

04:49.866 --> 04:51.599
Jessica is the one

04:51.601 --> 04:53.701
who handles the bonuses
for the partners.

04:53.703 --> 04:55.703
I'm not talking
about a bonus check.

04:55.705 --> 04:58.640
I'm talking about a buy-in check
for a senior partnership.

04:58.642 --> 05:02.444
As founding partner,
I'm entitled to name

05:02.446 --> 05:06.314
one new senior partner
a year.

05:06.316 --> 05:08.516
I'm naming you.

05:14.924 --> 05:18.059
You're making--
you're--

05:18.061 --> 05:20.361
you're making me...
- Yes.

05:22.000 --> 05:28.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

05:29.138 --> 05:31.339
I can't wait
to tell everybody.

05:31.341 --> 05:33.575
My mother, my father,
Rabbi Shimkoff...

05:33.577 --> 05:36.644
Yes.

05:36.646 --> 05:40.482
Oh, my God, the look
on Harvey's face!

05:40.484 --> 05:42.383
Louis...

05:42.385 --> 05:44.486
It's official
as of this moment.

05:44.488 --> 05:46.221
But I think we should
make the actual announcement

05:46.223 --> 05:48.423
at the next
senior partners meeting.

05:48.425 --> 05:49.757
Sure, the meeting where

05:49.759 --> 05:50.859
the managing partner
will be voted on.

05:50.861 --> 05:53.361
I believe that is
on the agenda.

05:53.363 --> 05:57.599
Best to do these things
face to face, don't you agree?

05:57.601 --> 06:00.835
It's our secret.

06:00.837 --> 06:02.537
Tomorrow's just like
any other Tuesday.

06:02.539 --> 06:04.506
Exactly.

06:04.508 --> 06:09.077
Hey, congratulations.

06:09.079 --> 06:12.847
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

06:12.849 --> 06:16.117
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

06:16.119 --> 06:19.254
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

06:19.256 --> 06:22.991
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

06:22.993 --> 06:25.994
♪ living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

06:25.996 --> 06:29.998
♪ me and missus
so busy, busy making money ♪

06:30.000 --> 06:31.366
♪ all right

06:31.368 --> 06:36.938
♪ all that time
imagine this ♪

06:36.940 --> 06:38.139
♪ the greenback boogie ♪

